Kerry Hamilton was diagnosed with leiomyosarcoma, a rare cancer of the soft tissue normally found in women over 50 . 
  She had experienced spotting in between her periods and stomach cramps for two years . 
  Doctors finally discovered she had a tumour the size of a golf ball in her cervix . 
  She was forced to have a hysterectomy and is now raising awareness of rare cancers . 
  Ms Hamilton began experiencing odd symptoms in 2009 when she flew to South Africa to volunteer at a lion research centre . 
 